
TCP/IP Model
🎯 Objective

Learn the TCP/IP model, understand the function of each layer, identify the protocols used at each layer, and understand how data travels across the Internet.

What is the TCP/IP Model?

The TCP/IP (Transmission Control Protocol/Internet Protocol) model is the standard networking model used for communication over the Internet. It defines how devices communicate, send, receive, and route data between networks.

Unlike the OSI model, which has 7 layers, the TCP/IP model has 4 layers and is widely used in real-world networking.

